# Roasted Fennel, Sweet Potato, Garlic Salad

_Cuisine:  American_<br />
_Course:  Side Dish_

## Ingredients

- 2 fennel bulbs, sliced
- 1 head garlic
- 1 sweet potato, diced
- 1 red bell pepper
- 1 lemon zest
- salt and pepper, to taste
- olive oil
- 2 tbsp balsamic vinegar
- 4 tbsp olive oil
- 1 lemon, juiced
- hot sauce, to taste
- salt
- 2/3 bag of kale

## Instructions

1. Pre-heat oven to 350 F.
1. Slice **fennel**, cut **garlic head** in half, dice **sweet potato** and dice **red bell pepper**.
1. Place **vegetables** in a bowl and toss with **lemon zest**, **salt**, **pepper**, and some **olive oil**.
1. Spread **vegetables** on a parchment lined baking sheet and roast at 350 F for 25 minutes.
1. In a glass measuring cup, make the salad dressing by whisking together **balsamic vinegar**, **olive oil**, **lemon juice**, **hot sauce**, and **salt**.
1. When the **vegetables** are done, toss with **kale** and **dressing** in a large bowl.

